trans-unit.source: Provides data for the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.ChildChanged"></xref> and <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost.ChildChanged"></xref> events.

The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ChildChangedEventArgs> class is used by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost> and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost> classes when the values of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName> properties change.
Use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ChildChangedEventArgs.PreviousChild%2A> property to get the previously assigned child control or element.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ChildChangedEventArgs"></xref> class.
The value of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.Child"></xref> property before the new value was assigned.
Gets the value of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.Child"></xref> property before the new value was assigned.
The value of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.Child"></xref> property before the new value was assigned.
